values: So even though I was going to use my LJ for photography and artistic thingamajigs, I just had to take a moment and post a picture of the place I was proposed to over the weekend...just for my own girlish amusement.  ;-)
(The next two are from a butterfly exhibit where you walk amidst hundreds of different butterflies)

I'm a huge fan of dreams.

I keep a dream journal and write in it even if it's only a split second of a dream.  It's fun to go back later and read what I was dreaming about years ago...most of them I don't even remember, and I think to myself, "Where in the world did that come from?"  So then I thought about it some more today, and I wondered, where do my dreams come from?

It's like this:  the other day I was on ebaumsworld and saw a picture of a champion hula hooper with what looked like a hundred hula hoops going around her body all at once.  So that night, I had a dream that some random, fictional dream lady gave me a hula hoop and told me to practice with it until she finished a phone call.  Obviously, I know what prompted that dream.  But what I'm wondering is, why would that conjure up a really weird dream in my brain while, say, the "Dramatic Chipmunk" video on youtube failed to make me have a strange dream involving chipmunks making funny faces and suspense music in the background?
Update Journal
It's just odd to me, because as much as I love thinking about dreams and what causes them and all that kind of stuff...I just don't understand how the most miniscule, split second of an event from a whole 16 hour day could make me have an entire dream based solely on that insignificant occurrence.  And I'm not really into psychology, so I don't know anything about it in that aspect...but on a different level, I'm baffled.

:-/

After that first post, I decided it's a better idea to actually post something.  No rambling.  I need to make that my rule if I'm really going to do this.  So, I'm posting some pictures...at least, a few that I'm actually proud of having taken.

Okaaayyyy.  I finally got this thing going.  I'm still not really sure about it.  I like Blogger a lot better because (a) it's ad free, and (b) it feels more like a real blog than this.  But I'm going to try this out as a means of just goofing off and joining communities.  We'll see how it goes.  

*Wishing myself luck*
